26/11/2004
ROME, Italy -- Interior Minister Giuseppe Pisanu met with his Greek counterpart, Public Order Minister Giorgos Voulgarakis, on Thursday (25 November). They discussed common efforts in the fight against illegal immigration, crime and terrorism. They expressed satisfaction with the level of co-operation between their respective police and security services. They also agreed illegal immigration is the most acute problem at hand, vowing to further strengthen patrols of land and sea borders. (ANA - 25/11/04)
